cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the routing complexity and performance of handover operations in access networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also evaluates and analyzes edge distance distributions in various regions, which involves the use of network measurements and analysis (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the findings for mobile unicast and multicast routing, which relates to network protocols and algorithms (cs.CR) and system and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses traceroute to collect packet forwarding path and round-trip-time, which involves the use of distributed computing (cs.DC).
